sub_topic: Identifying the automorphism group of a graph.
message_1: Consider a graph G with 6 vertices and 8 edges. Find the automorphism group of the graph G.
message_2:
To find the automorphism group of the graph G with 6 vertices and 8 edges, we first need to know the structure of the graph. Since there are multiple possible graphs with 6 vertices and 8 edges, we cannot determine the automorphism group without more information about the specific graph.

An automorphism group of a graph is a set of all permutations of the vertices that preserve the adjacency relations between the vertices. In other words, it is a group of all isomorphisms of the graph to itself.

If you can provide more information about the structure of the graph G, I can help you find the automorphism group.
